in a beauty parlor.

51:21.400 --> 51:24.358
I'm doing hair, Tony.
Do you remember Hiram Gonzalez?

51:24.600 --> 51:27.239
His father owned that barbershop.
It's his place.

51:27.320 --> 51:29.834
Plus I go to junior college.
Miami Dade.

51:30.000 --> 51:32.912
In two more years,
I get my cosmetology license.

51:33.000 --> 51:36.151
- Then I'll be making enough money...
- Surprise!

51:36.720 --> 51:39.359
All that's over, starting today.

51:39.760 --> 51:40.749
Why?

51:40.840 --> 51:45.311
My kid sister don't have to work
in no beauty parlor, and Mama...

51:45.920 --> 51:48.229
she don't have to sew in no factory.

51:48.520 --> 51:50.556
Your son made it, Mama.

51:51.920 --> 51:53.194
He's a success.

51:54.320 --> 51:56.629
That's why
I didn't come around before.

51:57.520 --> 52:01.274
I want you to see
what a good boy I've been.

52:03.600 --> 52:04.999
Here's $1,000.

52:05.800 --> 52:07.153
For you, Mama.

52:14.680 --> 52:16.796
Who did you kill for this, Antonio?

52:17.640 --> 52:19.471
I didn't kill nobody, Mama.

52:20.400 --> 52:21.469
No?
No.

52:22.440 --> 52:24.317
What are you doing now?

52:24.880 --> 52:27.838
<i>Banks, or is it still bodegas,
you and the others?</i>

52:27.920 --> 52:30.070
No! Things are different now.

52:30.160 --> 52:32.879
I'm working
with an anti-Castro group.

52:33.240 --> 52:34.798
I'm an organizer now.

52:34.880 --> 52:37.075
I get a lot
of political contributions.

52:38.080 --> 52:39.513
Sure you do.

52:43.760 --> 52:46.718
A gun sticking in somebody's face
is how.

52:48.280 --> 52:51.158
You know, all we hear about
in the papers...

52:52.920 --> 52:55.753
is animals like you
and the killings.

52:56.440 --> 52:59.591
It's Cubans like you who are giving
a bad name to our people.

52:59.680 --> 53:02.877
People who come here, work hard
and make a good name for themselves.

53:02.960 --> 53:04.837
People who send their children
to school.

53:04.920 --> 53:06.558
What are you saying?
That's your son...

53:06.640 --> 53:09.598
Son? I wish I had one.

53:10.400 --> 53:11.389
He's a bum.

53:11.480 --> 53:14.199
He was a bum then
and he's a bum now.

53:16.120 --> 53:17.838
Who do you think you are?

53:20.280 --> 53:23.113
We haven't heard a word
from you in five years.

53:26.080 --> 53:28.674
You suddenly show up here,
throw some money around...

53:28.760 --> 53:31.115
and think you can get my respect.

53:31.680 --> 53:34.319
You think you can buy me
with jewellery?

53:34.400 --> 53:37.836
You think you can come into my house
with your hotshot clothes...

53:37.920 --> 53:40.309
and your jail manners
and make fun of us?

53:40.400 --> 53:44.359
- You don't know what you're saying.
- That's not the way I am, Antonio!

53:44.560 --> 53:46.949
That is not the way
I raised Gina to be!

53:49.000 --> 53:51.355
You are not going to destroy her.

53:52.960 --> 53:54.632
I don't need your money.

53:56.640 --> 53:58.392
I work for my living.

53:58.920 --> 54:01.388
I don't want you
in this house anymore!

54:01.840 --> 54:03.717
I don't want you around Gina.

54:04.600 --> 54:07.194
So come on. Get out!

54:18.320 --> 54:22.154
And take this lousy money with you.
It stinks.

54:25.000 --> 54:27.753
Why do you have to spoil it
for everybody?

54:30.280 --> 54:31.872
<i>I'm sorry, Tony.</i>

54:33.560 --> 54:34.879
Okay, Mama.

54:39.000 --> 54:40.433
No. Tony, wait a minute!

54:40.520 --> 54:42.590
Don't go, please!
Gina, stay here!

54:42.840 --> 54:44.876
No, Mama.
He's no good. Gina!

54:46.120 --> 54:47.872
Tony, wait, please!

54:48.480 --> 54:52.758
I'm sorry. I don't know.
Mama, ever since Papa left she's...

54:52.840 --> 54:54.910
Forget Papa. We never had one.

54:55.120 --> 54:57.554
I know you did some bad things
back then.

54:57.800 --> 55:00.394
In the Army,
I know you got into some trouble.

55:00.480 --> 55:02.152
The Communists...

55:02.240 --> 55:04.231
they're always trying
to tell you what to do.

55:04.320 --> 55:07.039
- Mama doesn't understand that.
- I know.

55:08.600 --> 55:11.068
I just... I don't know.

55:11.160 --> 55:13.628
I just want you to know
that I don't care.

55:13.920 --> 55:17.629
<i>It doesn't matter to me how long
you've been away, five or ten years.</i>

55:19.640 --> 55:22.712
You're my blood, always.

55:23.880 --> 55:24.949
I know.

55:35.040 --> 55:38.112
- Come on. I want you to take this.
- I gotta go back in.

55:38.200 --> 55:40.794
- No, Tony. Please.
- You need this.

55:40.880 --> 55:42.154
What will I tell her?

55:42.240 --> 55:43.912
Take that.
You don't tell her anything.

55:44.000 --> 55:47.390
Don't tell her I gave it to you,
but give her some from time to time.

55:47.480 --> 55:49.994
And listen, you go out yourself.

55:50.080 --> 55:53.356
Go ahead, go out, do some things.
Have some fun.

55:53.520 --> 55:55.590
You gotta get some fun out of life.

55:55.680 --> 55:58.399
You gonna beat yourself to death
at 19?

55:58.480 --> 56:00.869
A pussycat like you? Come here.

56:05.120 --> 56:06.917
- I'll talk to you again.
- Okay.

56:07.000 --> 56:09.036
Put that money away.
Don't let her see it.

56:09.120 --> 56:10.553
I'll talk to her.

56:12.400 --> 56:13.753
I'll talk to you.

56:15.800 --> 56:16.835
Let's go.

56:18.760 --> 56:20.990
She's beautiful. How come you...

56:23.640 --> 56:27.519
Stay away from her. You hear?

56:28.280 --> 56:29.554
She's not for you.

56:38.400 --> 56:43.428
COCHABAMBA, BOLIVIA

56:55.280 --> 56:58.238
So, this and my other factory,
I can guarantee production...

56:58.320 --> 57:02.233
of 200 kilos refined
every month of the year.

57:02.680 --> 57:04.830
The problem is,
I have no steady market.

57:04.920 --> 57:08.196
Basically, what I'm looking for
is somebody in the States...

57:08.280 --> 57:11.511
who can share the risk with me,
somebody who can guarantee...

57:11.600 --> 57:15.639
to buy from me, say,
150 kilos a month.

57:17.040 --> 57:20.157
That's a big commitment, Mr. Sosa.
Something like that...

57:21.200 --> 57:23.430
Too bad Frank's not here.
You should talk to him.

57:23.520 --> 57:26.478
- It would've been nice if he'd come.
- He would like to come...

57:26.560 --> 57:30.951
but with his trial coming up,
it's hard to leave the country.

57:31.040 --> 57:34.316
- So he sent you instead?
- Something like that.

57:34.400 --> 57:36.550
We'll talk at my house, shall we?

57:37.160 --> 57:40.436
You got good stuff here.
Class-A shit.

58:01.400 --> 58:04.995
This Lopez guarantees
to buy 150 kilos from me...

58:05.080 --> 58:06.308
every month of the year.

58:06.400 --> 58:07.549
He picks it up here.

58:07.640 --> 58:09.790
I can sell it to him
for as little as...

58:11.640 --> 58:14.950
$7,000 a key.
You can't do better than that.

58:15.760 --> 58:18.479
But then we got to take the risk
of moving it.

58:18.680 --> 58:21.513
We'll be cutting out the Colombians.
Know what that means?

58:21.600 --> 58:23.431
That means we have
to go to war with them.

58:23.520 --> 58:26.557
We cut out the Colombians,
we take risks on both sides.

58:27.040 --> 58:28.837
Why don't we split the risk?

58:30.440 --> 58:33.830
You guarantee your delivery,
say, as far as Panama...

58:34.640 --> 58:36.312
we take it from there.

58:38.560 --> 58:41.836
Panama is risky. It costs me more.

58:43.440 --> 58:47.513
Panama I can sell for $13,500 a key.

58:48.720 --> 58:51.154
$13,500? What, are you nuts?

58:52.680 --> 58:56.150
$13,500? We still
got to take that shit to Florida.

58:56.240 --> 58:58.276
<i>Do you know
what that's like these days?</i>

58:58.360 --> 59:00.351
You got the Navy everywhere.

59:00.520 --> 59:04.672
You got frogmen. You got EC-2s
with the satellite-tracking shit.

59:05.280 --> 59:08.397
You got the fucking Bell 209
assault choppers up the ass.

59:08.880 --> 59:11.269
We're losing one
out of every nine loads.

59:12.200 --> 59:14.998
That's no duckwalk anymore,
let me tell you.

59:15.200 --> 59:16.599
Forget about $13,500.

59:20.000 --> 59:22.639
What do you suggest
that is reasonable?

59:28.000 --> 59:29.956
Excuse me. One moment.

59:34.240 --> 59:36.470
What the fuck's the matter with you?

59:36.560 --> 59:38.152
Are you negotiating for Frank Lopez?

59:38.240 --> 59:40.390
Don't worry about it. Take it easy.

59:40.480 --> 59:43.392
I'm not worried about it.
You should worry about it.

59:43.960 --> 59:46.679
If he wants to make a deal,
it's up to him, not you.

59:46.760 --> 59:48.273
We're doing this one deal.
That's it.

59:48.360 --> 59:50.191
Fuck you. How's that?

59:51.320 --> 59:52.958
- Fuck you.
- Fuck you.

59:53.080 --> 59:55.719
You need to open your eyes
and keep your mouth shut.

59:55.800 --> 59:58.598
That's it. Let it go at that.
Don't worry about it.

59:58.680 --> 01:00:01.831
Your head's in the wrong place.
You must watch out for yourself.

01:00:01.920 --> 01:00:03.069
<i>Why not talk to him?</i>

01:00:03.160 --> 01:00:05.037
<i>You think he wants
to give you the money?</i>

01:00:05.120 --> 01:00:06.519
Shut the fuck up.

01:00:06.600 --> 01:00:08.591
I'm doing the talking here, not you.

01:00:09.400 --> 01:00:11.914
You're here to watch my back.
Watch my back.

01:00:13.320 --> 01:00:15.231
Better than your front,
let me tell you.

01:00:15.320 --> 01:00:16.719
<i>That's easier to watch.</i>

01:00:16.800 --> 01:00:18.153
Close your mouth.

01:00:18.520 --> 01:00:21.637
I can't wait to see what Frank's
gonna react to this one.

01:00:22.200 --> 01:00:24.668
Just shut up.
I'm doing the talking here.

01:00:25.880 --> 01:00:28.235
Now where were we?
Panama.

01:00:28.680 --> 01:00:30.830
You're looking for a partner, right?

01:00:32.160 --> 01:00:33.639
Something like that.

01:00:33.720 --> 01:00:37.076
Look, Mr. Sosa,
we're getting ahead of ourselves.

01:00:37.720 --> 01:00:41.759
I am down on Frank's authority
to buy 200 keys, that's it.

01:00:42.000 --> 01:00:44.195
That's my limit. I got no right.

01:00:44.280 --> 01:00:47.238
- Nobody got no right to negotiate...
- Let the man finish, okay?

01:00:47.320 --> 01:00:49.914
Let him propose a proposition,
then we can talk more.

01:00:50.000 --> 01:00:51.911
You got no authority here.

01:00:52.000 --> 01:00:54.673
I started you in this business,
so shut the fuck up.

01:00:54.760 --> 01:00:58.594
- Frank is gonna love it.
- That's up to Frank, not you!

01:01:02.040 --> 01:01:03.996
I'm sorry about this, Mr. Sosa.

01:01:04.440 --> 01:01:05.919
No, it is all right.

01:01:06.440 --> 01:01:09.557
You're right.
Maybe you should talk to Frank.

01:01:12.320 --> 01:01:13.389
Well, good.

01:01:14.680 --> 01:01:17.672
I don't think it's something
I want to do on an overseas phone.

01:01:17.960 --> 01:01:22.670
But as soon as I get back to Miami,
I will talk to Frank personally.

01:01:23.760 --> 01:01:24.749
Good.

01:01:25.480 --> 01:01:27.789
My associates can escort you
to my chopper...

01:01:27.880 --> 01:01:29.518
<i>to take you to Santa Cruz.</i>

01:01:29.600 --> 01:01:32.558
<i>I have a jet there.
You'll be in Miami in five hours.</i>

01:01:32.640 --> 01:01:35.518
You'll be back here tomorrow
in time for lunch.

01:01:37.040 --> 01:01:38.075
Good.

01:01:41.760 --> 01:01:43.318
Good talking to you.

01:01:44.320 --> 01:01:46.356
Why not leave your friend here?

01:01:46.440 --> 01:01:49.113
While you're gone, he can tell me
how to run my business.

01:01:49.200 --> 01:01:52.158
- I think Frank wants to see him.
- No, that's okay.

01:01:52.240 --> 01:01:55.755
You tell Frank I'm keeping this guy
on ice for him.

01:01:58.400 --> 01:01:59.879
I guess so.

01:02:03.000 --> 01:02:04.752
Let's finish our lunch.

01:02:09.080 --> 01:02:11.196
I have to hand it to you, Mr. Sosa.

01:02:12.520 --> 01:02:14.670
You got everything a man could want.

01:02:16.560 --> 01:02:19.233
I like you, Tony.
There is no lying in you.

01:02:20.760 --> 01:02:24.753
Unfortunately, I don't feel the same
about the rest of your organization.

01:02:28.160 --> 01:02:30.310
What do you mean by that, Mr. Sosa?

01:02:30.960 --> 01:02:33.269
I'm talking about Omar Suarez.

01:02:35.880 --> 01:02:39.236
This garbage was recognized
by my associate at lunch...

01:02:40.160 --> 01:02:42.435
<i>from several years ago in New York.</i>

01:02:46.560 --> 01:02:48.596
He was an informer for the police.

01:03:05.720 --> 01:03:09.793
He put Vito Duval and Nello
and Gino Ramos away for life.

01:03:14.240 --> 01:03:16.959
<i>So how do I know
you're not a chivato, too, Tony?</i>

01:03:23.720 --> 01:03:25.870
Let's get this straight now.

01:03:27.520 --> 01:03:31.513
I've never fucked anybody over
who didn't have it coming.

01:03:31.760 --> 01:03:33.079
You got that?

01:03:34.000 --> 01:03:37.629
All I have in this world
is my balls and my word.

01:03:37.760 --> 01:03:40.991
I don't break them for no one,
you understand?

01:03:42.080 --> 01:03:44.594
That piece of shit up there,
I never liked him...

01:03:44.680 --> 01:03:46.113
I never trusted him.

01:03:46.320 --> 01:03:48.231
For all I know, he had me set up...

01:03:48.320 --> 01:03:50.595
and had my friend
Angel Fernandez killed.

01:03:50.680 --> 01:03:52.989
But that's history.
I'm here, he's not.

01:03:53.080 --> 01:03:55.355
You want to go on with me, say it.

01:03:55.440 --> 01:03:58.079
You don't, then you make a move.

01:04:03.520 --> 01:04:06.080
I think you speak from the heart,
Montana.

01:04:06.160 --> 01:04:07.513
<i>But I say to myself...</i>

01:04:08.560 --> 01:04:10.471
this Lopez, your boss...

01:04:11.480 --> 01:04:14.233
<i>he had chivatos like that
working for him.</i>

01:04:15.120 --> 01:04:16.678
His judgment stinks.

01:04:19.080 --> 01:04:20.991
So I think to myself...

01:04:21.400 --> 01:04:24.278
how many other mistakes
has this Lopez guy made?

01:04:26.600 --> 01:04:30.388
How can I trust his organization?
You tell me, Tony.

01:04:32.640 --> 01:04:35.393
Frank is smart, you know?

01:04:37.760 --> 01:04:39.910
You can't blame him for that animal.

01:04:41.080 --> 01:04:43.753
It's a crazy business we're in,
you know?

01:04:43.840 --> 01:04:46.479
That could happen to anyone,
even you.

01:04:52.680 --> 01:04:55.433
Why don't I go back
and talk to Frank...

01:04:56.360 --> 01:04:57.793
and work it out?

01:04:58.640 --> 01:05:00.517
I'll fix things between us.

01:05:02.360 --> 01:05:03.918
You got my word on that.

01:05:05.480 --> 01:05:08.233
I think you and me,
we can work this thing out...

01:05:08.840 --> 01:05:11.149
we do business together
for a long time.

01:05:13.080 --> 01:05:14.354
Just remember...

01:05:15.320 --> 01:05:17.390
I'll only tell you one time...

01:05:18.600 --> 01:05:20.431
don't fuck me, Tony.

01:05:22.960 --> 01:05:24.871
Don't you ever try to fuck me.

01:05:38.160 --> 01:05:39.388
You what?

01:05:41.520 --> 01:05:44.876
You made a deal
for fucking $18 million...

01:05:44.960 --> 01:05:46.234
without even checking with me?

01:05:46.320 --> 01:05:48.311
Are you crazy, Montana?
Are you crazy?

01:05:48.400 --> 01:05:50.118
<i>- Coño. Take it easy.
